Sentencas: In this study, Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC) nanofiber materials were prepared by electrospinning for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ nanofibers as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: We presented an efficient strategy for fabricating fiber electrodes with a good three-dimensional network structure using PVP as a softening agent.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ nanofibers as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SSC nanofibers prepared by electrospinning method have good contact with the electrolyte and excellent electrochemical performance as SOFCs cathode material.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ nanofibers as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared to the SSC nanoparticles cathode, the cathodic polarization resistance of SSC nanofiber cathode decreased by 32.3%, 27.9%, 27.7%, and 12.1% at 500 degrees C, 550 degrees C, 600 degrees C, and 650 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ nanofibers as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is proposed that the high-voltage electric field can inhibit the Sr bias on the surface of the material, which favoring the migration of oxygen ions and electrons.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ nanofibers as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, in a single cell with SSC nanofiber electrodes, we achieved a maximum power density of 0.494 W/cm2 and 0.766 W/cm2 at 600 degrees C and 650 degrees C, respectively, which demonstrating good electrochemical output performance.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ nanofibers as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
